From the Infowars web site :: Katherine Albrecht hosts the Alex Jones Show on this Monday, March 4 edition. Katherine talks with Adrian Salbuchi, an internationally-renowned Argentine author, political analyst, speaker and radio and television commentator, and Lenore Skenazy, a columnist, author, and reality show host who gained national notoriety when she let her then-9-year-old son take the New York City Subway home alone. Katherine Albrecht is the founder of Consumers Against Supermarket Privacy Invasion and Numbering and hosts a radio GCN Radio network Monday through Friday and Saturday.
